caption: I wanted to use this coupon I had so I ordered a Turkey Club on a croissant minus the tomato, a large soup of Turkey Kale with Rice (it is their best soup and I hadn't had it in years-this location was the only 1 that had it which is why I chose to go here) and a medium Strawberry Lemonade. My coupon was for $5 off $15 or more so I ordered online and was set to go pick it up. Parking around there is horrible so after a few attempts driving around I found a spot. I went inside and was told that they didn't have the Turkey Kale soup and they offered me another soup. Imagine my disappointment because that was the main reason I even chose to get Au Bon Pain today, so this now affected my order because I didn't want to substitute it for anything else. I now wanted a refund for it and the lemonade because now the coupon is useless. The guy in the store said that I would have to call the customer service number to request a refund for it (which I did while I was there). I told the guy in store that I only wanted the sandwich but he let me keep the lemonade for free and I thanked him. I was just really looking forward to that Turkey Kale soup and I did receive the refund via an email notification later that day.

The next time I try the sandwich, I just may venture out for bacon.

Visited this place sometime last week of December, between 9am and 10am. The place have ample space, tables, and stand-in area.  Customer Service: The staff looks friendly, and they are nice, nothing wrong with the team  Food: We ordered their soup and half-sandwich menu item. We like the sandwich and soup. We have tried Chicken Noodle Soup, Chicken Florentine and Chicken Vegetable Soup. All 3 were superb, very hearty, tasty and delicious. The same goes for the sandwich, the bread tastes great and fresh. They also offer coffee which is freshly made.  Place: Ample space for ~20 people . Several tables are spread around the area, not too noisy, and clean. It is also bright, have enough natural light, and looks nice.  They are in great location, I like it, very easy to visit by foot or other means.  Price: For the serving size and for the taste compared to other food shops in the area, it's reasonable and affordable. I understand that it's DC but I paid about ~$8 for each soup and it's a fair price. Planning to go back again to this shop!
